    </section>

    <!-- Playing Style Section -->
    <section class="style-section" id="style">
      <div class="section-container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <span class="section-label">On The Pitch</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Playing Style</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="style-grid">
          <div class="style-card fade-in">
            <div class="style-icon">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                <line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="16"></line>
                <line x1="8" y1="12" x2="16" y2="12"></line>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="style-title">Target Man</h3>
            <p class="style-description">
              At 6'2", Barlow serves as a classic target striker who can hold up play and
              bring teammates into the attack. His physical presence makes him a focal point
              in the final third, capable of winning aerial duels and shielding the ball into
              dangerous areas.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="style-card fade-in">
            <div class="style-icon">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"></polygon>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="style-title">Explosive Pace</h3>
            <p class="style-description">
              Despite his size, Barlow possesses tremendous speed and can generate significant
              steam on runs in open space. This combination of height and pace makes him a
              dual threat—equally dangerous in aerial battles and running in behind defensive
              lines.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="style-card fade-in">
            <div class="style-icon">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <path
                  d="M4 15s1-1 4-1 5 2 8 2 4-1 4-1V3s-1 1-4 1-5-2-8-2-4 1-4 1z"
                ></path>
                <line x1="4" y1="22" x2="4" y2="15"></line>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="style-title">Work Rate</h3>
            <p class="style-description">
              Known for leaving "everything on the field," Barlow is an impactful defender
              from the forward position. His pressing and tracking back fit perfectly into
              modern tactical systems that demand high-energy contributions from all
              positions.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="style-card fade-in">
            <div class="style-icon">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                <path d="M12 16v-4"></path>
                <path d="M12 8h.01"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="style-title">Aerial Threat</h3>
            <p class="style-description">
              Statistical strength in aerial duels makes Barlow dangerous on set pieces. His
              ability to win headers in the box and execute flick-ons creates opportunities
              for teammates while keeping defenders honest on crosses and corners.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="style-card fade-in">
            <div class="style-icon">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path>
                <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle>
                <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path>
                <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="style-title">Team Player</h3>
            <p class="style-description">
              A player of high character who prioritizes team success over personal
              statistics. His direct approach and willingness to do whatever the team needs
              make him a valuable squad member who can change games from the bench or the
              starting lineup.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="style-card fade-in">
            <div class="style-icon">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"></path>
                <path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"></path>
                <path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="style-title">MLS Experience</h3>
            <p class="style-description">
              With nine MLS seasons under his belt, Barlow brings invaluable experience in
              the Eastern Conference. He understands the league's unique demands and has
              proven himself against the best competition MLS has to offer.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Career Timeline -->
    <section class="timeline-section" id="career">
      <div class="section-container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <span class="section-label">Journey</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Career Timeline</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item current fade-in">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2026 - Present</div>
            <div class="timeline-title">FC Cincinnati</div>
            <div class="timeline-subtitle">MLS - Eastern Conference</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              Signed as a free agent on January 12, 2026. Attracted by FCC's winning culture,
              world-class TQL Stadium, and passionate fanbase. Ready to contribute to the
              club's continued pursuit of MLS Cup glory.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item fade-in">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2024 - 2025</div>
            <div class="timeline-title">Chicago Fire FC</div>
            <div class="timeline-subtitle">MLS - Eastern Conference</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              Two seasons in the Windy City provided valuable experience and a career-defining
              moment—a hat trick against D.C. United in June 2025, earning his first MLS
              Player of the Matchday award.
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-stats">
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">50</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Appearances</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">5</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Goals</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item fade-in">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2019 - 2023</div>
            <div class="timeline-title">New York Red Bulls</div>
            <div class="timeline-subtitle">MLS - Eastern Conference</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              Five seasons with the Red Bulls shaped Barlow into the player he is today.
              Developed in their famous high-pressing system, he scored on his MLS debut
              against Atlanta United and accumulated valuable playoff experience with 3
              postseason goals.
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-stats">
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">140</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Apps (All Comps)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">18</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Goals</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">3</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Playoff Goals</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item fade-in">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2018 - 2019</div>
            <div class="timeline-title">New York Red Bulls II</div>
            <div class="timeline-subtitle">USL Championship</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              Dominated at the USL level, showcasing prolific goal-scoring ability that earned
              his promotion to the first team. His time with Red Bulls II proved he could find
              the net consistently when given playing time.
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-stats">
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">42</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Appearances</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">21</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Goals</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">4</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Assists</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item fade-in">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2014 - 2017</div>
            <div class="timeline-title">University of Wisconsin</div>
            <div class="timeline-subtitle">NCAA Division I</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              Four stellar seasons as a Wisconsin Badger, where Barlow's physical attributes
              and goal-scoring prowess caught the attention of MLS scouts. Selected 39th
              overall in the 2018 MLS SuperDraft.
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-stats">
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">78</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Appearances</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">23</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Goals</span>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-stat">
                <span class="timeline-stat-value">10</span>
                <span class="timeline-stat-label">Game Winners</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item fade-in">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">Youth</div>
            <div class="timeline-title">St. Louis Scott Gallagher</div>
            <div class="timeline-subtitle">Youth Academy - St. Louis, MO</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              Developed through one of America's premier youth soccer programs alongside
              notable talents. This is the same club where FC Cincinnati Head Coach Pat
              Noonan began his own soccer journey—a connection that adds special meaning to
              this move.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quotes Section -->
    <section class="quotes-section" id="quotes">
      <div class="section-container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <span class="section-label">In Their Words</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">What They're Saying</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="quotes-grid">
          <div class="quote-card fade-in">
            <p class="quote-text">
              "This opportunity made me want to join FC Cincinnati, because of what you guys
              have done here in the past few years. The winning culture, the amazing Stadium,
              the amazing fans, it's a dream come true to join this club."
            </p>
            <p class="quote-author">Tom Barlow</p>
            <p class="quote-role">On signing with FC Cincinnati</p>
          </div>
          <div class="quote-card fade-in">
            <p class="quote-text">
              "Tom is a forward with a wealth of experience in our league, and his skill set
              is an excellent addition to our attack. He's a player of high character and a
              great teammate."
            </p>
            <p class="quote-author">Chris Albright</p>
            <p class="quote-role">FC Cincinnati General Manager</p>
          </div>
          <div class="quote-card fade-in">
